      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Hierarchical decomposition organises a complex goal into a tree: the root is the goal, internal nodes are compound tasks that need further breakdown, and leaves are primitive tasks executable by a single agent call. Unlike a flat DAG, the tree structure captures the full nesting of sub-goals and enables level-aware context passing, bottom-up result aggregation, and dynamic depth control."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Hierarchical decomposition tree: root goal splits into L1 compound tasks (Build Backend, Build Frontend, Deploy), each decomposed into L2 primitive leaf tasks executed directly"
        }
      },
